https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MRNGw08i6S4&list=PLg5SS_4L6LYvN1RqaVesof8KAf-02fJSi&index=10&t=1s

- types of services:
ClusterIP - IP only inside k8s cluster
NodePort - some port on all k8s workers
ExternalName - DNS Name Record
LoadBalance - for cloud cluster (AWS, GCP, AZURE)

1. create deployment:
kubectl create delployment <name> --image <image>
 
2. create replicas:
kubectl scale deployment <deployment_name> --replica <amount>

3. Provide access, create service:
kubectl expose deployment <deployment_name> --type=<type> --port 80

4. list services:
kubectl get services or get svc

5. delete service:
kubectl delete service <name>

- Provide access, create service:
kubectl expose deployment <deployment_name> --type=NodePort --port 80
kubectl describe nodes | grep ExternalIP
kubectl get svc
externalIp:port

- Provide access, create service:
kubectl expose deployment <deployment_name> --type=LoadBalancer --port 80
kubectl get svc



